com.camerontec.catalys.util.fast.template.instruction

Interface IRuntimeInstruction

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IInstruction
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ByteVectorCopy, ByteVectorDefault, ByteVectorDelta, ByteVectorNoOp, ByteVectorTail, ConstantInstruction, CopyBase, DecimalCopy, DecimalDefault, DecimalDelta, DecimalIndividualOperators, DecimalNoOp, DefaultBase, DeltaBase, DeltaBytesBase, IncrementBase, Int32Copy, Int32Default, Int32Increment, Int32NoOp, Int64Copy, Int64Default, Int64Increment, Int64NoOp, IntegerDelta, RuntimeInstruction, StringAsciiCopy, StringAsciiDefault, StringAsciiDelta, StringAsciiNoOp, StringAsciiTail, StringUnicodeDelta, TailBase, TemplateIDInstruction, Uint32Copy, Uint32Default, Uint32Increment, Uint32NoOp, Uint64Copy, Uint64Default, Uint64Increment, Uint64NoOp, UnicodeCopy, UnicodeDefault, UnicodeNoOp, UnicodeTail

    public interface IRuntimeInstruction
extends IInstruction
    A run time instruction knows how to decode its associated field into into a message using a particular type of FAST instruction - consisting of at least a FAST type, a FAST operator and other related instruction attributes (eg whether or not a field is optional).

    Run time instructions are preconfigured with external run time objects that it needs in order to run. These objects which are only known at run time include input and output streams.

    Author:
    John Cameron

    • Method Detail

      • decode

        ITagValue decode(IFastDecodableMessage msg,
                 PmapContext pmapContext)
          throws IOException,
                 FastCodecException
        Decodes this instruction, returning the decoded value.

        The value object returned is taken from the given message.

        Unless this is a subinstruction (see setSubInstruction(boolean)), the value is also added to the given message.

        Parameters:
        msg - Message that we decode into
        pmapContext - Current PMAP context.
        Returns:
        Returns tag value containing decoded value. May be null if nothing was found.
        Throws:
        IOException - if there is a problem reading the stream.
        FastCodecException - If there is a problem decoding the value.

      • setSubInstruction

        void setSubInstruction(boolean subInstruction)
        Sets subinstruction flag.

        The only subinstructions are the exponent and mantissa instructions of a Decimal.

        If an instruction is a subinstruction, it does not automatically add itself to the message in a decode(com.camerontec.catalys.util.fast.message.IFastDecodableMessage, com.camerontec.catalys.util.fast.data.PmapContext) instruction.

        Parameters:
        subInstruction - True if this is a sub instruction.
